text: Baroness Birgitte Caroline "Nena" von Schlebrügge (born January 8, 1941) is a Swedish-German model. She was active from the 1950s and 1960s. She started her high-fashion modelling career in London in 1957. She worked at Vogue and Harper's Bazaar. Her daughter is actress Uma Thurman. She modeled for ‘Famntaget’ (‘The Embrace’) in Sweden. ==References== Category:1941 births Category:Living people Category:Mexican models Category:Naturalized citizens of the United States Category:Swedish models Category:Models from New York City Category:People from Mexico City
